A bipartisan group of public officials in the state were arrested Thursday for taking thousands of dollars in bribes in exchange for political favors.
Three Democrats and Two republicans were charged after an investigation by New Jersey’s Office of Public Integrity and Accountability (OPIA).
“This is old-school political corruption at its worst— the kind that undermines the political process and erodes public faith in government.
In exchange for the money, O’Donnell allegedly agreed to hire the CW for city tax work if he won his mayoral race in Bayonne.
Cesaro is a accused of accepting bribes from the CW in exchange for tax work for Morris County and Parsippany-Troy Hills if Cesaro were elected.